18	2022-10-06	\N	Call In	Under contract to purchase, supposed to close today; have not gotten a walkthrough and haven't received a limited warranty. Builder and seller have been unresponsive to myself and my agent.	26	3
19	2022-10-06	\N	Email In	Your firm assisted us with the closing of our property at 1808 Flat Shoals Rd, SE in Atlanta in 2020.  \r\n\r\nRecently, with the rains, it was discovered that water would accumulate under the house and come up through the floorboards.  This was explained to me by the contractors and engineer that this condition must have been known by the previous owner as this would occur during any significant rainfall. \r\n\r\nI'm wondering if I could talk to someone about what, if any, options I might have to seek recourse.  Do you or your firm handle these matters?  If not, is there someone you recommend that can assist me?  I'm happy to hop on a call if you'd prefer to talk.  You can reach me at 925-683-9710 if you'd like to call me.  Thank you in advance for any assistance you can provide me.	25	3
20	2022-10-06	\N	Call Out	She is in a meeting, will call back later this morning.	26	3
21	2022-10-06	\N	Call Out	In a meeting. Will call me back	27	4
22	2022-10-06	\N	Call Out	Called back. Left voicemail	28	4
23	2022-10-06	\N	Call Out	We can’t negotiate with terrorists (my sister). My sister convinced my parents to sell their house in S. Ga. My sister sold her house, took the proceeds, bought a bigger house.  She used her down payment money, and they agreed to split the mortgage, on the deed with my sister, listed as co-borrowers. My sister moved out with her boyfriend; parents had to move to the senior living facility. The house needs to be sold; my sister is convinced she is entitled to 100% of the equity. \r\n\r\nMy position is, you get your deposit money back, any gain is split 50/50. She refuses to cooperate. I’ve been given power of attorney by my parents. Sister will deal with nobody but my father. My father has said he doesn’t have the physical and mental capabilities to deal with this. She has been pretty vile, threatened my parents with a lawsuit. She is hell-bent on going to court.\r\n\r\nI haven’t been able to agree to get the house listed. Could be resolved through mediation. Somebody needs to help her understand that her actions are harmful; causing my parents undue stress, on a fixed income, hoping to pay their. . .\r\n\r\nPaid $450k for the house. Sharon Austin estimates it to be worth $595 to $625, $200k gain? She put down about $100k. $300 owed. Leave about $100k per side. She wants all of the profit. She hasn’t articulated a basis for her clam for 100% of the profits. She says she had paid someone a lot of money to prepare her proposal. Senior living; parents are not senile.\r\n\r\nParents will be out of money in the next ten years in senior living.	24	3
24	2022-10-05	\N	Call In	##Former Landlord/Tenant\r\nClient left voicemail that her former landlord will not release security deposit. She wants guidance on what to do.	28	4
25	2022-10-06	\N	Call Out	Referred to LRIS	23	4
26	2022-10-06	\N	Call In	Vm	26	3
27	2022-10-06	\N	Call Out	Seller sold house to an investment conglomerate before date of closing.\r\n\r\nClosing atty: John Maurer; Seller: Dudi Elias; Seller agent - Avi Shmesh?\r\n\r\nConsidering whether to retain counsel.	26	3
28	2022-10-06	\N	Call In	Client said former landlord is trying to keep security deposit for painting the home. Lease had ended and rent was automatically taken out for $1800.00. It was on auto-pay through Zillow. Former Landlord claims he do not have that money. Ms. Wilderman says it cleared her account on Monday,10/3. Looking for assistance.	28	4
29	2022-10-06	\N	Call Out	* 2020 we closed a property\r\n* Bought house through self-directed IRA\r\n* No indication of any issues with drainage\r\n* I am in California\r\n* Sinkhole opened next to the house. We filled that\r\n* A couple of weeks ago, with big rains, water started accumulating\r\n* The gutters go straight into the ground, nothing connected to them, no inspection would reveal this\r\n* Water accumulates and comes up through the house, through the floorboards\r\n* This house was built in the 50s; any significant situation; they would have known about this\r\n* This particular problem is costing me $21,000 to fix\r\n* House is built without a foundation, straight on the ground\r\n* Will talk to his wife and decide whether to retain counsel	25	3
