905	2024-07-31	20:16:00	Email In	Good evening, my name is Julie Raker. Laura Carrillo gave me your name and said you might be able to help me.\r\nHere is my situation for reference. I bought a house with my fiancé in July of 2022. The deed was a right of survivorships deed with both of us owning 50%. He passed in December of 2023.  5 weeks before he passed, he did a quit claim to his 2 sons for his half, unbeknownst to me.\r\nThey have now threatened that if I don’t agree to sell, I cannot afford to buy them out, then they will take me to court. I agreed to sell, but the older one now has added a condition.\r\nWhen we bought the house , my fiancée put the down payment from the sale of his house.  It’s quite a large amount of money and his son expects me to forfeit that money and take it off the top.\r\nMy question is, am I entitled to 1/2 of the money from the sale even though I didn’t put anything into the down payment?  I feel like when we bought the house, and it was a right of survivorship, I took a risk if he passed of taking on all expenses. My fiancé didn’t have to put me on the deed originally, but he did because we were going to be married.\r\nHis son is constantly texting me and I feel very harassed at this point.\r\nI am a Gwinnett County teacher and honestly cannot afford to hire anyone, but I thought I would reach out. Thank you for your time and if I need to pay for a consultant I can do that.\r\nMy number is 7708330095.	361	9
